.TH "smp_call_function" 9 "smp_call_function" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
smp_call_function \- Run a function on all other CPUs.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" smp_call_function
.BI "(smp_call_func_t func "  ","
.BI "void *info "  ","
.BI "int wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "func" 12
The function to run. This must be fast and non-blocking.
.IP "info" 12
An arbitrary pointer to pass to the function.
.IP "wait" 12
If true, wait (atomically) until function has completed
on other CPUs.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0.

If \fIwait\fP is true, then returns once \fIfunc\fP has returned; otherwise
it returns just before the target cpu calls \fIfunc\fP.

You must not call this function with disabled interrupts or from a
hardware interrupt handler or from a bottom half handler.
